  "body": "### Component\r\n\r\nAnvil\r\n\r\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\r\n\r\n- [X] Foundry\r\n- [X] Foundryup\r\n\r\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\r\n\r\nforge 0.2.0 (e0a5372 2022-06-02T00:13:59.438564Z)\r\n\r\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\r\n\r\nanvil --fork-url https://eth-mainnet.alchemyapi.io/v2/<KEY>\r\n\r\n### Operating System\r\n\r\nmacOS (Apple Silicon)\r\n\r\n### Describe the bug\r\n\r\nAnvil returns the block number of the previous fork url when resetting the fork with a new URL.\r\n\r\nHere is a code to reproduce:\r\n```\r\nimport requests\r\nimport random\r\n\r\nr = requests.post(\r\n\t\"http://127.0.0.1:1234\",\r\n\tjson={\r\n\t    \"method\": \"hardhat_reset\",\r\n\t    \"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\",\r\n\t    \"id\": random.randint(1, 10000),\r\n\t    \"params\":[{\"forking\":{\"jsonRpcUrl\":\"https://eth-mainnet.alchemyapi.io/v2/<KEY>\"}}]\r\n})\r\n\r\nr = requests.post(\r\n\t\"http://127.0.0.1:1234\",\r\n\tjson={\r\n\t    \"method\": \"eth_chainId\",\r\n\t    \"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\",\r\n\t    \"id\": random.randint(1, 10000),\r\n})\r\nprint(r.json())  # returns 0x1 - mainnet\r\n\r\nr = requests.post(\r\n\t\"http://127.0.0.1:1234\",\r\n\tjson={\r\n\t    \"method\": \"eth_blockNumber\",\r\n\t    \"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\",\r\n\t    \"id\": random.randint(1, 10000),\r\n})\r\nprint(r.json())  # returns mainnet block\r\n\r\nr = requests.post(\r\n\t\"http://127.0.0.1:1234\",\r\n\tjson={\r\n\t    \"method\": \"hardhat_reset\",\r\n\t    \"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\",\r\n\t    \"id\": random.randint(1, 10000),\r\n\t    \"params\":[{\"forking\":{\"jsonRpcUrl\":\"https://eth-goerli.alchemyapi.io/v2/<KEY>\"}}]\r\n})\r\n\r\nr = requests.post(\r\n\t\"http://127.0.0.1:1234\",\r\n\tjson={\r\n\t    \"method\": \"eth_chainId\",\r\n\t    \"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\",\r\n\t    \"id\": random.randint(1, 10000),\r\n})\r\nprint(r.json())  # returns 0x5 - goerli\r\n\r\nr = requests.post(\r\n\t\"http://127.0.0.1:1234\",\r\n\tjson={\r\n\t    \"method\": \"eth_blockNumber\",\r\n\t    \"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\",\r\n\t    \"id\": random.randint(1, 10000),\r\n})\r\nprint(r.json())  # returns mainnet block - wrong\r\n```",
